card.name: Hungry Mist

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "If the air must feed, let it take the self-righteous." —Murat, death speaker

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "Fyndhorn is our home." —Kolbjörn, elder druid of the Juniper Order

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "It's strange, but I can feel it when the land is corrupted. I understand why the Autumn Willow is so protective." —Daria

card.name: Rabid Wombat

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "That which nourishes can also bind." —Gemma, Willow Priestess

card.name: Scryb Sprites
card.property: Flying

property.name: Flavor
property.value: The only sound was the gentle clicking of the faeries' wings. Then those intruders who were still standing turned and fled. One thing was certain: they didn't think the Scryb were very funny anymore.

card.name: Shambling Strider
card.property: {R} {G}: Shambling Strider gets +1/-1 until end of turn.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Freyalise forbid that any stranger should wander into the striders' territory.

property.value: "I hear there are bears—or spirits—that guard caravans passing through the forest." —Gulsen, abbey matron

card.name: Thicket Basilisk

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Moss-covered statues littered the area, a macabre monument to the basilisk's power.

card.name: Thorn Thallid
card.property: At the beginning of your upkeep, put a spore counter on Thorn Thallid. Remove three spore counters from Thorn Thallid: It deals 1 damage to any target.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "The danger in cultivating massive plants caught the elves by surprise." —Sarpadian Empires, vol. III

Activate this ability only once each turn.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "Blow, winds, and crack your cheeks! rage! blow!" —William Shakespeare, King Lear

card.name: Wyluli Wolf
card.property: {T}: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "When one wolf calls, others follow. Who wants to fight creatures that eat scorpions?" —Maimun al-Wyluli, diary

card.name: Yavimaya Ants

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "Few natural forces are as devastating as hunger." —Kaysa, elder druid of the Juniper Order

card.name: Adun Oakenshield

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "Centaurs will kill our aesthir if they can; they've always been enemies. Destroy the horse-people on sight." —Arna Kennerüd, Skyknight

card.name: Dakkon Blackblade

property.value: "My power is as vast as the plains, my strength is that of mountains. Each wave that crashes upon the shore thunders like blood in my veins." —Dakkon Blackblade, Memoirs

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "There will come soft rains, and spring shall be amongst us, a welcome friend." —Halvor Arenson, Kjeldoran priest

card.property: Green creatures you control get +0/+2.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Abandoning his sword to return to the lush forest of Pendelhaven, Jacques le Vert devoted his life to protecting the creatures of his homeland.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Ashnod found few willing to trade their humanity for the power she offered them.

card.name: Clockwork Beast

card.name: Copper Tablet

property.name: Flavor

card.name: Dragon Engine

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Those who believed the city of Kroog would never fall to Mishra's forces severely underestimated the might of his war machines.

property.value: An early inspiration for Urza, Tocasia's onulets contained magical essences that could be cannibalized after they stopped functioning.

property.value: "Knowing its origins, how could they have thought they could control it?" —Sorine Relicbane, Soldevi heretic

property.value: "This shield is a true rarity: an artifact whose purpose is obvious." —Arcum Dagsson, Soldevi machinist

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "My soldiers know that they need never fear for their protection." —King Darien of Kjeldor

property.name: Flavor
property.value: Flawed copies of relics from the Thran Empire, the su-chi were inherently unstable but provided useful knowledge for Tocasia's students.

card.name: Tawnos's Coffin

If you do, return the other exiled cards to the battlefield under their owner's control attached to that permanent.

card.name: Urza's Bauble

property.name: Flavor
property.value: When sorely wounded or tired, Urza would often retreat to the workshops of his apprentices. They were greatly amazed at how much better he looked each time he took a sip of water.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "The fortress is not what it seems." —Arcum Dagsson, Soldevi machinist

card.name: Winter Orb

card.name: Zuran Orb
card.property: Sacrifice a land: You gain 2 life.

property.name: Flavor
property.value: "I will go to any length to achieve my goal. Eternal life is worth any sacrifice." —Zur the Enchanter

property.name: Flavor
